WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.768 --> 00:00:11.854
[tense. eerie music playing]

2
00:00:11.937 --> 00:00:13.981
- Don't you fucking move.
- [cackling]

3
00:00:16.190 --> 00:00:18.861
- Nat. where'd your brother go?
- He's across the street.

4
00:00:19.361 --> 00:00:20.863
[Tom] No! No. no. no. no. no. I'll go.

5
00:00:20.946 --> 00:00:22.448
You go upstairs. my closet.

6
00:00:22.531 --> 00:00:23.740
The code is Nat's birthday.

7
00:00:23.824 --> 00:00:25.075
Natalie. call the police.

8
00:00:26.410 --> 00:00:28.996
[beeping]

9
00:00:35.169 --> 00:00:36.837
[breathing heavily] Here.

10
00:00:36.920 --> 00:00:38.005
[Nevaeh chuckles]

11
00:00:38.088 --> 00:00:39.798
She moves. shoot her.

12
00:00:42.217 --> 00:00:43.302
Don't.

13
00:00:47.014 --> 00:00:50.350
[sinister music playing]

14
00:00:51.810 --> 00:00:53.771
What would you like to do tomorrow?

15
00:00:54.938 --> 00:00:56.106
Anything you want.

16
00:00:58.650 --> 00:00:59.943
Can we go fishing again?

17
00:01:00.944 --> 00:01:03.030
I just want to spend time with you.

18
00:01:03.113 --> 00:01:05.115
[chuckles] Of course.

19
00:01:08.327 --> 00:01:09.703
You're with me now.

20
00:01:13.165 --> 00:01:14.374
You're my son.

21
00:01:17.002 --> 00:01:18.587
[breathes shakily]

22
00:01:20.798 --> 00:01:22.216
- [breathes shakily]
- What is that?

23
00:01:22.299 --> 00:01:25.886
It's a Wi-Fi jammer. She must have used it
to get past the alarms.

24
00:01:25.969 --> 00:01:27.179
[Anna] How do you know that?

25
00:01:27.262 --> 00:01:29.306
Oh. you didn't tell your mom
about our date?

26
00:01:34.144 --> 00:01:35.395
Nat. are they coming?

27
00:01:35.479 --> 00:01:36.814
[Nevaeh] Do you even know
how to use a gun?

28
00:01:36.897 --> 00:01:38.190
Shut your fucking mouth!

29
00:01:39.274 --> 00:01:41.026
You really wanna shoot me. don't you?

30
00:01:41.610 --> 00:01:42.778
Sit back down.

31
00:01:49.118 --> 00:01:50.619
[Nevaeh chuckles] You can't do it.

32
00:01:51.203 --> 00:01:52.496
[breathes shakily]

33
00:01:53.080 --> 00:01:55.833
- [yelps]
- God! Fuck you! [screaming]

34
00:01:57.167 --> 00:01:58.752
- [Natalie] It's okay.
- [Nevaeh] Fuck you!

35
00:02:02.172 --> 00:02:04.341
- [pounding on door]
- [Tom] Zack!

36
00:02:04.424 --> 00:02:06.593
- [sighs] What does this guy want?
- [pounding continues]

37
00:02:06.677 --> 00:02:07.678
- [Tom] Zack!
- It's okay.

38
00:02:07.761 --> 00:02:09.430
[Romeo barking]

39
00:02:09.513 --> 00:02:10.931
[exhales heavily]

40
00:02:14.935 --> 00:02:16.395
Zack! Where is he?

41
00:02:16.895 --> 00:02:18.355
- Oh. God.
- He was terrified.

42
00:02:18.439 --> 00:02:19.731
You stay the fuck away!

43
00:02:19.815 --> 00:02:20.816
Hey!

44
00:02:21.358 --> 00:02:22.818
Leave my dad alone.

45
00:02:22.901 --> 00:02:24.611
- Oh. stop it. Son. get out.
- No.

46
00:02:24.695 --> 00:02:26.613
- No. I'm not leaving.
- We're leaving. No. we're leaving!

47
00:02:26.697 --> 00:02:28.782
- You're hurting him. You're hurting him!
- [Zack] Dad!

48
00:02:28.866 --> 00:02:29.867
No! No. para!

49
00:02:29.950 --> 00:02:31.994
- You are hurting him! He's only a boy!
- [Zack] No. Stop. Stop.

50
00:02:32.077 --> 00:02:33.454
- You're coming home.
- No. I'm not.

51
00:02:33.537 --> 00:02:34.955
- Tom! You're hurting him.
- Yes. you are.

52
00:02:35.038 --> 00:02:36.373
- No. Dad.
- He's only a boy!

53
00:02:36.457 --> 00:02:38.375
[Zack] You can't let him take me back.
Oh. shit.

54
00:02:38.459 --> 00:02:40.002
He's not your son anymore. Tom.

55
00:02:40.085 --> 00:02:41.295
[singsongy] He's my son.

56
00:02:41.378 --> 00:02:42.713
- [grunts]
- [groans]

57
00:02:45.215 --> 00:02:46.341
[tires screech]

58
00:02:46.425 --> 00:02:48.051
- [grunts]
- [groans]

59
00:02:50.345 --> 00:02:53.015
- [grunts] Come here.
- [bystanders shouting]

60
00:02:53.098 --> 00:02:54.224
[grunts]

61
00:02:58.437 --> 00:03:00.189
[grunts. chuckles]

62
00:03:00.272 --> 00:03:01.648
- [grunting]
- [groaning]

63
00:03:01.732 --> 00:03:04.902
[neighbor]
Tom. stop! You're gonna kill him!

64
00:03:05.652 --> 00:03:08.947
[groaning. panting]

65
00:03:09.031 --> 00:03:10.240
[neighbor] He has a knife!

66
00:03:11.533 --> 00:03:12.618
Oh. my God. [gasps]

67
00:03:13.702 --> 00:03:14.870
[groans]

68
00:03:15.537 --> 00:03:19.082
- [police siren wails in distance]
- Dad. It's gonna be okay. Dad.

69
00:03:21.418 --> 00:03:22.419
You're gonna be okay.

70
00:03:26.131 --> 00:03:29.134
[eerie music playing]

71
00:04:36.869 --> 00:04:39.913
- [Ray] Did you have to assault the guy?
- The guy who kidnapped my son?

72
00:04:39.997 --> 00:04:42.583
The guy whose daughter was living
in the fucking walls of our house?

73
00:04:42.666 --> 00:04:43.709
That guy? Come on. man.

74
00:04:43.792 --> 00:04:45.586
Yeah. well.
at least he's not pressing charges.

75
00:04:45.669 --> 00:04:48.130
Yeah. so he can look like the bigger man.
He loves this.

76
00:04:48.213 --> 00:04:50.716
So what'd you tell the cops
about the shotgun hole in your wall?

77
00:04:50.799 --> 00:04:53.635
I told them the truth. That he drugged us
and there was an accident.

78
00:04:53.719 --> 00:04:54.720
[scoffs]

79
00:04:55.429 --> 00:04:56.805
[sighs] You know.

80
00:04:56.889 --> 00:05:00.559
they found these vials in the walls.
some kind of motion sickness thing.

81
00:05:00.642 --> 00:05:03.520
If it shows up in Zack's blood.
maybe that's conspiracy.

82
00:05:03.604 --> 00:05:05.564
But there's no proof
Cady conspired. right?

83
00:05:05.647 --> 00:05:07.900
Nevaeh's still denying Max's involvement.

84
00:05:08.567 --> 00:05:12.571
I mean.
there is a world where we find proof.

85
00:05:13.197 --> 00:05:14.239
[Ray] Find?

86
00:05:14.323 --> 00:05:16.074
Nobody's finding anything.

87
00:05:16.158 --> 00:05:19.119
You're a little late to the party to be
wagging your finger. don't you think?

88
00:05:19.203 --> 00:05:20.996
You helped put us in this position.
you know?

89
00:05:21.079 --> 00:05:23.624
I know. I was wrong about Max.

90
00:05:23.707 --> 00:05:25.918
I fucked up and I'm sorry.

91
00:05:26.001 --> 00:05:28.128
But we have to be smart.

92
00:05:28.212 --> 00:05:32.591
It's not much.
but the woman with the face mask.

93
00:05:32.674 --> 00:05:34.593
the one you said
maybe knew stuff about Max…

94
00:05:35.260 --> 00:05:38.430
I got her plates from
the security cam off that hotel in Macon.

95
00:05:38.931 --> 00:05:41.892
Her name's Val Tierney.
from Piney Grove. North Carolina.

96
00:05:42.851 --> 00:05:44.228
Isn't that near where Cady grew up?

97
00:05:44.311 --> 00:05:45.729
And Amy Brancato.

98
00:05:46.230 --> 00:05:48.232
[Ray] Maybe she knew him from back then.

99
00:05:48.774 --> 00:05:53.195
Well. if that woman has any evidence
that Max made Amy falsely confess.

100
00:05:53.278 --> 00:05:55.697
- I mean. that's obstruction of justice.
- Well. that's something.

101
00:05:56.198 --> 00:05:57.324
- [Tom] We'll go with you.
- [Ray] Yeah.

102
00:05:57.407 --> 00:06:00.619
No. You two can't afford
to make another mistake.

103
00:06:00.702 --> 00:06:02.955
- Ray will go see Val. You two...
- I'm not just gonna sit here

104
00:06:03.038 --> 00:06:04.164
doing nothing. Noa.

105
00:06:04.248 --> 00:06:05.874
[Noa] You're not the only ones
who want him gone.

106
00:06:05.958 --> 00:06:07.751
This motherfucker's balls deep

107
00:06:07.835 --> 00:06:09.962
in the organization
I spent my whole life building.

108
00:06:10.546 --> 00:06:12.047
So. we're gonna get him.

109
00:06:12.131 --> 00:06:14.633
- [phone buzzing]
- But we're going to do it right.

110
00:06:16.427 --> 00:06:18.720
Hello. Yes.

111
00:06:18.804 --> 00:06:19.805
It's the hospital.

112
00:06:20.431 --> 00:06:22.766
What… [stammers] How is he?
Can we see him now?

113
00:06:24.518 --> 00:06:26.061
Uh. yeah. we're on our way.

114
00:06:28.564 --> 00:06:30.232
- All right.
- [Louis] Anna Deveraux

115
00:06:30.315 --> 00:06:32.860
and Tom Bowden met in law school.

116
00:06:32.943 --> 00:06:35.779
Was Anna pregnant by her fiancé.

117
00:06:35.863 --> 00:06:38.282
or by her old law school classmate Tom?

118
00:06:39.575 --> 00:06:40.909
How long do I have to stay here?

119
00:06:40.993 --> 00:06:44.663
I promised your mom I'd keep you safe
until the situation is resolved.

120
00:06:44.746 --> 00:06:48.167
- [groaning. grunting on phone]
- Jesus. Look. it's on Citizen.

121
00:06:51.587 --> 00:06:53.839
I always knew Tom had issues.

122
00:06:54.339 --> 00:06:55.591
[Natalie] Why do you hate him so much?

123
00:06:55.674 --> 00:06:56.800
[chuckles] I don't hate Tom.

124
00:06:57.509 --> 00:06:59.344
Yeah. he's wound too tight. and…

125
00:07:00.095 --> 00:07:03.182
Is it 'cause he and Mom were
sleeping together while you were engaged?

126
00:07:05.017 --> 00:07:06.435
Is he my real dad?

127
00:07:08.896 --> 00:07:10.606
Why are you asking me this now?

128
00:07:11.315 --> 00:07:13.358
Why are you not just saying no?

129
00:07:13.442 --> 00:07:15.944
[pensive music playing]

130
00:07:16.528 --> 00:07:17.529
Well…

131
00:07:18.781 --> 00:07:19.823
I think you're mine.

132
00:07:20.616 --> 00:07:21.784
[chuckles]

133
00:07:22.576 --> 00:07:23.869
Are you serious?

134
00:07:24.995 --> 00:07:27.706
Look. if you want me to say
I'm a hundred percent sure

135
00:07:27.790 --> 00:07:29.708
that I'm your biological dad. I will.

136
00:07:35.964 --> 00:07:37.216
[sighs]

137
00:07:38.091 --> 00:07:40.177
Great. Mom's here to pick me up.

138
00:07:40.928 --> 00:07:43.263
- Already? She said...
- Call her if you don't believe me.

139
00:07:50.479 --> 00:07:52.815
We're not trying to get him out.
We're just trying to see our son.

140
00:07:52.898 --> 00:07:54.108
[doctor] Our hands are tied.

141
00:07:54.191 --> 00:07:58.028
I'm sorry. but this is how
an involuntary psych hold works.

142
00:07:58.695 --> 00:08:00.322
Right now. he is not well.

143
00:08:01.198 --> 00:08:04.201
Tom. he stabbed you
and he's having a dissociative episode.

144
00:08:04.701 --> 00:08:06.912
So he's still saying he's…

145
00:08:06.995 --> 00:08:08.330
[inhales deeply]

146
00:08:08.413 --> 00:08:09.998
…Max Cady's kid?

147
00:08:10.791 --> 00:08:11.834
Yes.

148
00:08:12.668 --> 00:08:15.003
Listen. of all the drugs in his system.

149
00:08:15.087 --> 00:08:18.465
the one that worries me
the most is the scopolamine.

150
00:08:18.549 --> 00:08:19.800
Do you know what that is?

151
00:08:20.801 --> 00:08:22.928
That's the. uh. motion sickness thing?

152
00:08:23.011 --> 00:08:28.642
It is. yes. but in larger doses. it can
cause compliance or depersonalization.

153
00:08:29.309 --> 00:08:32.771
You give someone scopolamine
if you wanna take control of them

154
00:08:32.854 --> 00:08:34.522
or erase their personality.

155
00:08:35.649 --> 00:08:37.067
She brainwashed him.

156
00:08:38.234 --> 00:08:41.697
That's not a clinical term. but yes.

157
00:08:41.780 --> 00:08:43.365
[eerie music playing]

158
00:08:43.449 --> 00:08:45.868
Well. what's the recovery time?

159
00:08:47.286 --> 00:08:49.872
Well. we have no idea
how much of this stuff Zack was given

160
00:08:49.955 --> 00:08:53.667
or for how long or if the drugs
exacerbated a preexisting condition.

161
00:08:53.750 --> 00:08:55.586
[stammers] Preexisting like what?

162
00:08:56.545 --> 00:08:59.882
[doctor] What I mean is
that someone with underlying issues.

163
00:08:59.965 --> 00:09:02.593
if they have prolonged exposure
to this drug.

164
00:09:03.510 --> 00:09:05.721
it could cause permanent psychosis.

165
00:09:07.806 --> 00:09:09.183
Permanent psychosis?

166
00:09:24.823 --> 00:09:25.824
Tom?

167
00:09:28.577 --> 00:09:29.787
[Tom] I. uh…

168
00:09:30.788 --> 00:09:32.456
I had this dream the other night.

169
00:09:34.750 --> 00:09:35.751
I was 14.

170
00:09:36.627 --> 00:09:39.213
It was the summer
before my brother went to college.

171
00:09:40.380 --> 00:09:41.590
And we're all at dinner.

172
00:09:43.509 --> 00:09:45.094
And my dad says…

173
00:09:47.471 --> 00:09:50.390
"Your brother's gonna die
over Thanksgiving break.

174
00:09:50.474 --> 00:09:52.726
[emotional music playing]

175
00:09:52.810 --> 00:09:55.437
He's gonna come home
and get in a car crash and die."

176
00:09:58.315 --> 00:09:59.817
And my mother says.

177
00:10:01.485 --> 00:10:02.486
"That's right.

178
00:10:03.529 --> 00:10:04.530
He is."

179
00:10:07.366 --> 00:10:08.909
And I looked at both of them and I said.

180
00:10:08.992 --> 00:10:11.411
"Well. aren't you gonna do anything?"
[inhales shakily]

181
00:10:12.913 --> 00:10:14.498
And they don't even look at me.

182
00:10:16.708 --> 00:10:18.085
And I look at my brother.

183
00:10:18.794 --> 00:10:23.215
but his face is… blank. He's f-frozen.

184
00:10:25.884 --> 00:10:27.553
And then I realized he's not my brother.

185
00:10:27.636 --> 00:10:29.555
He's my… [sobs]

186
00:10:43.110 --> 00:10:44.111
[phone buzzing]

187
00:10:52.828 --> 00:10:54.496
[Anna] Hey. Natalie. is everything okay?

188
00:10:54.580 --> 00:10:55.622
[Natalie] I have a question.

189
00:10:56.331 --> 00:10:58.041
Have you been lying to me my whole life?

190
00:10:58.125 --> 00:10:59.126
[tense music playing]

191
00:10:59.209 --> 00:11:01.295
Natalie. it is really crazy right now.

192
00:11:01.378 --> 00:11:03.297
and when you call me.
I assume that something...

193
00:11:03.380 --> 00:11:05.632
Paul said he doesn't know
if he's my real dad.

194
00:11:08.260 --> 00:11:10.137
Well. I don't know why
he would say something like that.

195
00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:13.223
So is it true?

196
00:11:13.307 --> 00:11:14.808
Do you know who my dad is?

197
00:11:16.018 --> 00:11:18.812
Tom is your dad because he raised you.

198
00:11:18.896 --> 00:11:20.731
Paul is your biological dad.

199
00:11:22.191 --> 00:11:24.276
So you took a paternity test?

200
00:11:24.359 --> 00:11:27.029
That's a horrible thing
to ask your mother. You know that. right?

201
00:11:27.112 --> 00:11:28.113
Why?

202
00:11:28.197 --> 00:11:29.698
You want me to stop asking questions.

203
00:11:29.782 --> 00:11:33.535
but you've made me so complicit
in all your bullshit.

204
00:11:34.620 --> 00:11:36.997
- What do you mean by that?
- There are people that are saying

205
00:11:37.080 --> 00:11:39.792
that you and Tom got together
during the trial.

206
00:11:39.875 --> 00:11:41.168
and if anyone knew about that...

207
00:11:41.251 --> 00:11:42.336
No. no. that's not...

208
00:11:42.419 --> 00:11:44.046
Then Max would've been released years ago.

209
00:11:44.129 --> 00:11:45.839
No. Natalie. you need to stop it.

210
00:11:45.923 --> 00:11:48.217
Am I basically
the product of your misconduct.

211
00:11:48.300 --> 00:11:50.886
and you lied to me
because you had to lie to everyone else?

212
00:11:50.969 --> 00:11:53.555
You need to stop reading lies
on the Internet.

213
00:11:53.639 --> 00:11:54.890
You need to get off your phone

214
00:11:54.973 --> 00:11:56.225
and you need to stay at Paul's

215
00:11:56.308 --> 00:11:57.768
until it's safe to come home.

216
00:11:58.644 --> 00:12:01.271
Okay. Mom. I'll stay at Paul's.

217
00:12:06.819 --> 00:12:08.195
[knocks on door]

218
00:12:10.781 --> 00:12:11.990
Natalie?

219
00:12:13.200 --> 00:12:14.743
I just saw you came home.

220
00:12:15.786 --> 00:12:18.789
Listen. this guy keeps coming over.

221
00:12:20.165 --> 00:12:21.625
And I brought it back to you.

222
00:12:24.002 --> 00:12:25.003
[chuckles]

223
00:12:25.087 --> 00:12:27.089
Say. "Hi. Natalie.

224
00:12:28.257 --> 00:12:29.550
I wanna go home."

225
00:12:31.343 --> 00:12:33.262
[chuckles] Okay.

226
00:12:34.012 --> 00:12:35.013
[cat meows]

227
00:12:47.401 --> 00:12:48.652
[Natalie] Hi.

228
00:12:54.700 --> 00:12:55.909
Thanks for bringing him.

229
00:12:57.870 --> 00:12:58.871
Sure.

230
00:13:05.085 --> 00:13:06.086
Are you okay?

231
00:13:07.087 --> 00:13:08.505
Yeah. ah! [stammers]

232
00:13:08.589 --> 00:13:10.299
Yeah. I'm okay. Are you okay?

233
00:13:11.675 --> 00:13:12.718
Why wouldn't I be?

234
00:13:14.970 --> 00:13:18.599
All right. you believe your parents. okay.

235
00:13:20.100 --> 00:13:23.771
You think I told that girl to do
all those things to you. right?

236
00:13:23.854 --> 00:13:25.689
"That girl" as in your daughter?

237
00:13:27.316 --> 00:13:29.234
Who lived in my walls
and drugged my brother?

238
00:13:29.318 --> 00:13:31.945
But did she tell the police
that I made her do that stuff?

239
00:13:32.029 --> 00:13:35.407
- No. but...
- Did she tell you I made her do it?

240
00:13:36.116 --> 00:13:37.534
She didn't need to. It makes sense.

241
00:13:37.618 --> 00:13:38.786
[Max] Oh. it makes sense.

242
00:13:39.620 --> 00:13:42.414
Hmm. Well. uh. I'm not sure about that.

243
00:13:42.498 --> 00:13:44.833
Here. Look at this.

244
00:13:44.917 --> 00:13:46.126
[eerie music playing]

245
00:13:46.210 --> 00:13:49.671
She was obsessed
with the idea of me as her father.

246
00:13:49.755 --> 00:13:54.760
and she thought if she got revenge for me.
that I would love her.

247
00:13:55.677 --> 00:13:57.888
You see that?
And I told her to leave you alone.

248
00:13:59.014 --> 00:14:00.182
She needs help.

249
00:14:03.268 --> 00:14:04.561
Wow.

250
00:14:04.645 --> 00:14:05.729
[Max] "Wow." Yeah.

251
00:14:06.814 --> 00:14:07.815
All right.

252
00:14:08.649 --> 00:14:09.650
Bye.

253
00:14:09.733 --> 00:14:11.193
Can I ask you something?

254
00:14:12.736 --> 00:14:16.240
Uh… I'm sorry that she hurt you.
but that's all I know.

255
00:14:17.783 --> 00:14:19.785
It's not about Nevaeh. It's about my mom.

256
00:14:21.078 --> 00:14:23.789
[stammers] That's a conversation
for you and her.

257
00:14:24.456 --> 00:14:25.457
I have to go.

258
00:14:26.750 --> 00:14:28.001
Max. this is important.

259
00:14:28.085 --> 00:14:31.088
Yeah. but I have to get
on the road. [chuckles]

260
00:14:40.764 --> 00:14:43.600
[dark. mysterious music playing]

261
00:14:43.684 --> 00:14:47.980
[beeping]

262
00:15:01.660 --> 00:15:04.079
[ominous music playing]

263
00:15:30.063 --> 00:15:31.398
Hey.

264
00:15:32.274 --> 00:15:33.275
I'm coming with you.

265
00:15:34.026 --> 00:15:35.778
But you don't know where I'm going.

266
00:15:37.029 --> 00:15:38.030
It's a drive.

267
00:15:38.655 --> 00:15:41.950
Well. you said to come back if I asked
my mom and she doesn't answer.

268
00:15:42.451 --> 00:15:43.994
I did and she didn't. so…

269
00:15:44.077 --> 00:15:46.497
[chuckles] Well. I'm glad you trust me.

270
00:15:47.748 --> 00:15:48.957
Well. I didn't say that.

271
00:15:49.041 --> 00:15:50.709
I already shared
my location with my friend.

272
00:15:50.793 --> 00:15:53.128
so if anything happens to me.
she'll call 911.

273
00:15:53.212 --> 00:15:54.296
Oh. all right.

274
00:15:54.880 --> 00:15:56.381
- I'm serious.
- I hear you.

275
00:15:56.465 --> 00:15:57.883
If you insist.

276
00:15:58.467 --> 00:15:59.468
Come in.

277
00:16:10.729 --> 00:16:13.732
["(Don't Fear) The Reaper" playing]

278
00:16:24.326 --> 00:16:26.328
[music continues on radio]

279
00:16:27.496 --> 00:16:30.707
Everyone says my mom was different
back when she was your lawyer.

280
00:16:30.791 --> 00:16:32.584
Mmm. [chuckles]

281
00:16:33.085 --> 00:16:35.838
Maybe she just got better at hiding.

282
00:16:38.549 --> 00:16:39.842
What's that mean?

283
00:16:41.677 --> 00:16:43.887
Your mom was always…

284
00:16:46.098 --> 00:16:50.352
doing everything she could
to hide from herself.

285
00:16:53.772 --> 00:16:54.982
[sighs]

286
00:16:56.775 --> 00:16:58.527
- Like drinking?
- Mm-hmm.

287
00:17:01.947 --> 00:17:02.948
And other stuff?

288
00:17:03.532 --> 00:17:06.534
[chuckles] "Other stuff."

289
00:17:06.618 --> 00:17:07.619
[chuckles]

290
00:17:07.703 --> 00:17:10.121
Uh. you know. uh…

291
00:17:11.123 --> 00:17:12.916
What was the name of her fiancé?

292
00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:15.168
Paul? Right? Paul?

293
00:17:16.043 --> 00:17:18.254
Well. that guy was not faithful to her.

294
00:17:18.338 --> 00:17:21.716
so why should she show
some respect to that guy?

295
00:17:21.800 --> 00:17:23.719
How do you know he wasn't faithful?

296
00:17:24.845 --> 00:17:25.846
She told me.

297
00:17:31.059 --> 00:17:32.144
When I met her.

298
00:17:33.937 --> 00:17:39.067
we both. uh. thought
that my wife had left me and. um…

299
00:17:41.445 --> 00:17:44.031
we became quite close.

300
00:17:48.410 --> 00:17:52.831
But then police found my wife's body.
and something changed.

301
00:17:56.126 --> 00:17:57.211
[sighs]

302
00:18:00.172 --> 00:18:01.173
[Max] Mmm.

303
00:18:01.256 --> 00:18:03.258
[music continues]

304
00:18:05.344 --> 00:18:06.345
[music ends]

305
00:18:06.428 --> 00:18:09.431
[downcast music playing]

306
00:18:09.515 --> 00:18:11.517
[birds chirping]

307
00:18:12.518 --> 00:18:13.769
Hey.

308
00:18:16.438 --> 00:18:18.107
What happened to our son?

309
00:18:36.416 --> 00:18:37.417
[sighs]

310
00:18:38.585 --> 00:18:41.588
[mysterious music playing]

311
00:18:47.052 --> 00:18:48.387
- [knocks on door]
- Hello?

312
00:18:50.889 --> 00:18:51.890
Hello?

313
00:18:53.767 --> 00:18:54.768
[sighs]

314
00:18:56.895 --> 00:18:58.105
[door opens]

315
00:18:59.481 --> 00:19:00.524
Hey. hello.

316
00:19:00.607 --> 00:19:01.608
Hi.

317
00:19:02.401 --> 00:19:03.569
Is Val Tierney home?

318
00:19:04.445 --> 00:19:05.779
Who's asking?

319
00:19:05.863 --> 00:19:10.159
[Ray] I'm looking for the owner of
a 1994 Plymouth Reliant K Station Wagon.

320
00:19:10.826 --> 00:19:13.662
Ray Rawlins. Liberty State Insurance.

321
00:19:14.455 --> 00:19:18.000
You may be entitled to a class action
settlement from overcharged premiums.

322
00:19:18.083 --> 00:19:19.376
Oh. shit.

323
00:19:19.460 --> 00:19:21.044
I sold it for cash.

324
00:19:21.128 --> 00:19:23.380
- Is that girl gonna get my settlement?
- [chuckles]

325
00:19:23.464 --> 00:19:26.258
Don't worry about that. Look. An advance.

326
00:19:27.384 --> 00:19:28.510
Don't tell my boss.

327
00:19:30.429 --> 00:19:31.472
Who'd you sell it to?

328
00:19:31.555 --> 00:19:33.766
I'd be careful if I was you.

329
00:19:34.475 --> 00:19:36.935
She's a fucking fruit loop.

330
00:19:37.019 --> 00:19:40.063
Been in and out
of this and that clinic for years.

331
00:19:40.564 --> 00:19:41.774
Yeah? What's her name?

332
00:19:42.357 --> 00:19:44.860
[sighs] Her name is Crystal Cady.

333
00:19:45.611 --> 00:19:47.112
- Crystal Cady?
- Mm-hmm.

334
00:19:47.196 --> 00:19:48.655
[intriguing music playing]

335
00:19:48.739 --> 00:19:50.157
Was she married to Max Cady?

336
00:19:50.783 --> 00:19:52.367
She's his sister.

337
00:19:53.786 --> 00:19:55.078
- His sister?
- Mm-hmm.

338
00:19:56.205 --> 00:19:58.040
Wait. is this her?

339
00:19:58.832 --> 00:19:59.875
Let me see.

340
00:19:59.958 --> 00:20:01.043
[tense music playing]

341
00:20:01.126 --> 00:20:04.421
Hmm. It's hard to tell with that mask on.

342
00:20:05.839 --> 00:20:08.258
Oh. yeah. Mm-hmm. That's her.

343
00:20:09.551 --> 00:20:11.011
[sighs] Poor girl.

344
00:20:13.514 --> 00:20:15.390
If-If she wasn't locked up.

345
00:20:17.142 --> 00:20:18.268
where would she stay?

346
00:20:18.769 --> 00:20:20.771
["I'm Eighteen" playing]

347
00:20:22.106 --> 00:20:25.943
[groaning]

348
00:20:26.902 --> 00:20:27.903
[sighs]

349
00:20:29.113 --> 00:20:30.697
[groans]

350
00:20:33.492 --> 00:20:35.202
- You okay?
- Yeah. yeah. I'm fine.

351
00:20:40.332 --> 00:20:41.375
Where are we going?

352
00:20:41.458 --> 00:20:43.544
I told you it's a long drive.

353
00:20:44.670 --> 00:20:47.840
Remember. I shared my location.
so if anything happens. I…

354
00:20:47.923 --> 00:20:51.427
[Max] That's good. that's good.
You're a smart woman.

355
00:20:53.429 --> 00:20:55.597
Yeah. I like that. I like that.

356
00:20:57.266 --> 00:20:58.434
Are you kidnapping me?

357
00:21:04.940 --> 00:21:08.277
- [chuckles]
- [chuckles]

358
00:21:09.903 --> 00:21:12.114
Did I ask you to get in my car?

359
00:21:12.197 --> 00:21:15.576
[chuckles] No. I did not.

360
00:21:16.243 --> 00:21:19.413
[sighs] That was so funny.

361
00:21:20.122 --> 00:21:22.416
Now. uh. you wanna catch a bus home?

362
00:21:22.499 --> 00:21:23.667
- [chuckles]
- You can.

363
00:21:25.002 --> 00:21:26.211
Really. you can.

364
00:21:27.880 --> 00:21:29.548
But I'm glad you came.

365
00:21:30.716 --> 00:21:37.389
Because I'm. uh. going to visit
my parents where I grew up. and…

366
00:21:39.475 --> 00:21:40.476
[sighs]

367
00:21:40.559 --> 00:21:42.186
Isn't that in North Carolina?

368
00:21:42.269 --> 00:21:44.396
I told you it's a… [chuckles] …long drive.

369
00:21:44.480 --> 00:21:45.939
[chuckles. breathing heavily]

370
00:21:46.023 --> 00:21:48.734
And. uh. it's not going to be easy.

371
00:21:48.817 --> 00:21:52.571
So. I'm glad
I'm not taking this drive by myself.

372
00:21:56.784 --> 00:21:58.368
Why won't it be easy?

373
00:21:59.995 --> 00:22:01.121
Were they mean to you?

374
00:22:01.914 --> 00:22:04.708
Well. my father raised dogs.

375
00:22:08.295 --> 00:22:09.338
Litter.

376
00:22:09.421 --> 00:22:12.674
And. uh. like. uh.
if I didn't speak English.

377
00:22:12.758 --> 00:22:14.760
he would put me in a cage like a dog.

378
00:22:16.136 --> 00:22:17.137
Mm-hmm.

379
00:22:18.972 --> 00:22:20.641
Your mom wouldn't stop him?

380
00:22:20.724 --> 00:22:23.352
From a graveyard in Spain?
No. she couldn't.

381
00:22:23.435 --> 00:22:27.064
[chuckles] My stepmother
could have done something about it.

382
00:22:27.147 --> 00:22:30.067
but she didn't…
she didn't stop him either.

383
00:22:30.734 --> 00:22:32.903
Because to her I was an unwanted guest.

384
00:22:34.071 --> 00:22:35.197
[sighs] I'm so sorry...

385
00:22:35.280 --> 00:22:36.532
- [groaning]
- Max.

386
00:22:36.615 --> 00:22:37.908
- Fuck!
- Max!

387
00:22:37.991 --> 00:22:39.701
[groaning] Fuck!

388
00:22:40.410 --> 00:22:41.578
- Max!
- [tires screeching]

389
00:22:41.662 --> 00:22:43.872
- [horn honks]
- [groaning continues]

390
00:22:48.168 --> 00:22:50.504
[Natalie] Hit the brake! Hit the brake!

391
00:22:53.465 --> 00:22:55.634
- Natalie. the pills. The pills.
- What?

392
00:22:55.717 --> 00:22:57.428
The pills. The pills. here.

393
00:22:59.096 --> 00:23:01.056
- [gasps]
- [groans]

394
00:23:09.606 --> 00:23:11.191
- [whimpers]
- [groans]

395
00:23:11.775 --> 00:23:15.195
- [whimpering]
- [screams]

396
00:23:18.157 --> 00:23:19.324
[groaning]

397
00:23:21.660 --> 00:23:23.370
What was that? [pants]

398
00:23:23.454 --> 00:23:27.708
[exhales heavily] Oh. I get glitches.

399
00:23:27.791 --> 00:23:29.293
Sometimes I get glitches.

400
00:23:30.169 --> 00:23:34.465
Because in prison
they-they broke my-my skull here.

401
00:23:35.466 --> 00:23:37.926
Oh. fuck. This was horrible.

402
00:23:39.052 --> 00:23:40.262
Fuck.

403
00:23:40.345 --> 00:23:42.347
And your father hit me in the head.

404
00:23:43.432 --> 00:23:46.435
[scoffs] Fuck.

405
00:23:46.518 --> 00:23:48.145
That wasn't helpful.

406
00:23:49.062 --> 00:23:50.564
That wasn't helpful.

407
00:23:51.690 --> 00:23:52.816
[groans]

408
00:23:52.900 --> 00:23:55.319
What do you do
if you're alone when that happens?

409
00:24:03.327 --> 00:24:04.328
Wow.

410
00:24:05.913 --> 00:24:07.998
Wow… [stammers]
…that was brave of you. Natalie.

411
00:24:08.081 --> 00:24:10.709
Shit. Thank you. You okay?

412
00:24:11.502 --> 00:24:12.503
Yeah.

413
00:24:12.586 --> 00:24:13.754
- All right.
- Are you?

414
00:24:13.837 --> 00:24:15.255
- Yeah. I'm okay.
- [sighs]

415
00:24:16.381 --> 00:24:20.552
[sighs] It's better if you take the wheel.

416
00:24:21.595 --> 00:24:23.430
I need to rest.

417
00:24:24.765 --> 00:24:26.100
[exhales heavily]

418
00:24:26.183 --> 00:24:27.684
You have your license. right?

419
00:24:27.768 --> 00:24:29.645
[ominous music playing]

420
00:24:29.728 --> 00:24:31.897
- Yeah. I have my license.
- Okay.

421
00:24:34.942 --> 00:24:36.944
[eerie music playing]

422
00:24:40.864 --> 00:24:43.867
Cops didn't find all the scopolamine vials
she had in there.

423
00:24:44.451 --> 00:24:46.537
They gotta have Nevaeh's prints on them.

424
00:24:48.038 --> 00:24:52.292
If the police found them at Max's house.
it'll prove they conspired.

425
00:24:52.376 --> 00:24:53.669
You wanna frame him?

426
00:24:53.752 --> 00:24:56.088
Well. it's not a frame if he's guilty.

427
00:24:56.171 --> 00:24:57.881
Is that gonna be your defense?

428
00:24:57.965 --> 00:25:00.676
I'm not gonna need a defense
because I'm not gonna get caught.

429
00:25:00.759 --> 00:25:02.594
You don't think
the cops will know it is us

430
00:25:02.678 --> 00:25:05.472
if someone calls in a tip
about scopolamine at Max's house?

431
00:25:05.556 --> 00:25:07.891
Anna. the tip would say.
uh. heroin or coke.

432
00:25:07.975 --> 00:25:09.476
They would just find the scopolamine.

433
00:25:11.019 --> 00:25:12.396
Look. Max's car is gone.

434
00:25:12.479 --> 00:25:14.648
[stammers] I have to do this now.

435
00:25:14.731 --> 00:25:16.900
- Hey. whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa. hey.
- [stammers]

436
00:25:17.484 --> 00:25:19.278
Who's gonna protect our family
if you're in jail?

437
00:25:19.361 --> 00:25:20.946
Well. we can't just do nothing.

438
00:25:21.029 --> 00:25:23.198
Well. maybe we do move.
Maybe we sell the house. I...

439
00:25:23.282 --> 00:25:25.284
And-And do what when he follows us. huh?

440
00:25:25.367 --> 00:25:26.535
Move again?

441
00:25:27.578 --> 00:25:30.998
Spend every second scared for our kids
whenever they're out of sight?

442
00:25:32.249 --> 00:25:33.625
If you got a better plan. lay it on me

443
00:25:33.709 --> 00:25:35.294
because I swear to God
this is all I've got.

444
00:25:35.377 --> 00:25:36.628
Okay. okay. okay.

445
00:25:40.215 --> 00:25:42.009
But you are not breaking into Max's house.

446
00:25:42.092 --> 00:25:43.969
You have never done
anything like that before.

447
00:25:49.641 --> 00:25:51.477
But we do know someone who has.

448
00:25:55.481 --> 00:25:57.649
["Avant Gardener" playing]

449
00:26:10.496 --> 00:26:11.997
- [chuckles]
- What?

450
00:26:12.831 --> 00:26:15.334
[chuckles] I don't know.

451
00:26:16.418 --> 00:26:17.544
You seem…

452
00:26:19.296 --> 00:26:21.507
You seem relaxed. [chuckles]

453
00:26:24.510 --> 00:26:26.095
Just feels good to drive.

454
00:26:27.930 --> 00:26:29.348
Have a break from everything.

455
00:26:34.895 --> 00:26:36.897
Did you ever see Cape Fear River?

456
00:26:38.524 --> 00:26:40.109
Isn't it super polluted?

457
00:26:40.192 --> 00:26:42.111
No. I was baptized there.

458
00:26:43.112 --> 00:26:44.363
- In the river?
- Yeah.

459
00:26:44.446 --> 00:26:46.824
Right down there. At Bluff's Point.

460
00:26:46.907 --> 00:26:48.742
[ominous music playing]

461
00:26:48.826 --> 00:26:49.868
And. uh…

462
00:26:50.452 --> 00:26:52.079
Yeah. couldn't swim.

463
00:26:52.996 --> 00:26:54.581
Can't swim. actually.

464
00:26:55.415 --> 00:26:57.835
But my father made me do it.

465
00:26:58.752 --> 00:27:01.213
To wash away the sin. And. uh…

466
00:27:02.464 --> 00:27:03.882
Fuck. I was scared.

467
00:27:03.966 --> 00:27:05.968
I was so scared that I could drown.

468
00:27:07.761 --> 00:27:11.765
But you know what happened when I…
when I came out of the water?

469
00:27:14.226 --> 00:27:17.813
I was a different person. cleansed.

470
00:27:21.150 --> 00:27:22.818
I was not that boy anymore.

471
00:27:24.862 --> 00:27:26.029
But I was me.

472
00:27:44.798 --> 00:27:45.799
[engine stops]

473
00:27:58.604 --> 00:28:00.689
- [Natalie] This is where you grew up?
- [sighs]

474
00:28:05.986 --> 00:28:07.696
- I'll come with you.
- Stay. stay.

475
00:28:07.780 --> 00:28:08.781
I won't be long.

476
00:28:11.408 --> 00:28:14.328
[dog growls. barking]

477
00:28:16.038 --> 00:28:18.040
[dogs barking]

478
00:28:32.638 --> 00:28:33.639
[Natalie] Hello.

479
00:28:35.933 --> 00:28:38.352
Hi. hi.

480
00:28:38.435 --> 00:28:39.436
Oh. hey.

481
00:28:40.854 --> 00:28:43.607
Hi. baby. Look how cute you are.

482
00:28:45.567 --> 00:28:47.861
- What are you doing. huh?
- [suspenseful music playing]

483
00:28:47.945 --> 00:28:49.029
[Natalie] I'm sorry.

484
00:28:50.823 --> 00:28:51.949
[chuckles]

485
00:28:52.032 --> 00:28:54.535
How'd you like it
if I just came up and pet you?

486
00:28:56.578 --> 00:28:58.163
She… She seemed friendly.

487
00:28:58.789 --> 00:29:00.332
I'd wash my hands.

488
00:29:01.125 --> 00:29:02.209
She's got worms.

489
00:29:09.550 --> 00:29:10.592
I'm Natalie.

490
00:29:11.093 --> 00:29:12.428
Are these your dogs?

491
00:29:13.470 --> 00:29:14.555
No.

492
00:29:16.807 --> 00:29:18.350
But I get protective of them.

493
00:29:19.476 --> 00:29:20.602
That's nice.

494
00:29:22.062 --> 00:29:23.564
Especially the shy ones.

495
00:29:26.608 --> 00:29:30.028
Well. uh. I'm just waiting for someone.

496
00:29:30.112 --> 00:29:31.905
but I'm gonna go wait in the car.

497
00:29:32.489 --> 00:29:33.657
Can I kiss you?

498
00:29:37.119 --> 00:29:38.912
- Hmm?
- What?

499
00:29:41.123 --> 00:29:42.124
[sighs]

500
00:29:44.835 --> 00:29:45.836
Just one time.

501
00:29:46.670 --> 00:29:47.963
I have to go. I'm sorry.

502
00:29:53.385 --> 00:29:55.888
[wood creaking]

503
00:29:57.222 --> 00:29:59.224
[suspenseful music continues]

504
00:30:16.241 --> 00:30:17.493
Well. well. well.

505
00:30:18.452 --> 00:30:20.954
Look what the dog puked up.

506
00:30:28.796 --> 00:30:30.547
Somebody put you in your place. huh?

507
00:30:32.132 --> 00:30:33.217
Yeah.

508
00:30:34.218 --> 00:30:35.302
Like you used to…

509
00:30:37.221 --> 00:30:38.347
Papa.

510
00:30:39.348 --> 00:30:41.308
Don't make that mongrel noise to me.

511
00:30:43.811 --> 00:30:45.312
- [sighs]
- [dogs barking]

512
00:30:47.231 --> 00:30:49.900
Hey. hey! Keep your hands to yourself.

513
00:30:50.526 --> 00:30:53.362
Why don't you go back to
wherever the fuck it is you come from?

514
00:30:55.322 --> 00:30:58.075
Okay. Where… Where's Crystal?

515
00:31:00.744 --> 00:31:02.079
You fucked with her head enough.

516
00:31:03.288 --> 00:31:05.290
You come within spitting distance of her.

517
00:31:05.958 --> 00:31:07.376
I'm gonna fuck you up.

518
00:31:09.628 --> 00:31:12.381
I can make you tell me. old man.

519
00:31:12.464 --> 00:31:13.715
You know that.

520
00:31:14.758 --> 00:31:16.009
[scoffs]

521
00:31:17.594 --> 00:31:20.597
[laughing]

522
00:31:24.977 --> 00:31:27.813
You-You think you can make me do anything?

523
00:31:32.025 --> 00:31:33.861
Everything you know how to do.

524
00:31:35.654 --> 00:31:37.030
I knew it first.

525
00:31:41.910 --> 00:31:43.370
- Woof!
- [gasps]

526
00:31:45.247 --> 00:31:46.290
See?

527
00:31:47.374 --> 00:31:49.042
Yeah. you train a dog right…

528
00:31:51.420 --> 00:31:53.046
it'll never forget its master.

529
00:31:53.130 --> 00:31:55.299
[breathing shakily]

530
00:31:55.924 --> 00:31:58.927
- You still sit?
- [breathing shakily]

531
00:31:59.928 --> 00:32:01.930
Where the fuck is Crystal?

532
00:32:02.014 --> 00:32:03.098
Huh?

533
00:32:04.016 --> 00:32:05.642
How about you want the cage again?

534
00:32:06.351 --> 00:32:08.020
I still got it open for you.

535
00:32:09.563 --> 00:32:10.564
Sit.

536
00:32:11.940 --> 00:32:12.941
Roll over.

537
00:32:16.570 --> 00:32:18.238
Yeah. that's what I thought.

538
00:32:19.031 --> 00:32:20.157
You're nothing.

539
00:32:22.201 --> 00:32:23.702
You're just a sick little puppy.

540
00:32:23.786 --> 00:32:25.370
Couldn't stop pissing on the rug.

541
00:32:25.454 --> 00:32:27.456
That's why I had to smack ya nose.

542
00:32:28.040 --> 00:32:29.208
But you never learn nothing.

543
00:32:30.542 --> 00:32:33.629
I'm sorry.
There was this guy talking to me.

544
00:32:33.712 --> 00:32:34.963
[Robert] Oh. that's just Luke.

545
00:32:35.047 --> 00:32:36.799
He feeds the dogs.

546
00:32:39.468 --> 00:32:41.053
Who's this?

547
00:32:41.136 --> 00:32:42.513
A little young. don't you think?

548
00:32:42.596 --> 00:32:43.597
Come here.

549
00:32:44.848 --> 00:32:46.391
Why don't you go back down to Savannah.

550
00:32:46.475 --> 00:32:48.936
hang out with that Deveraux girl
who put you away?

551
00:32:49.019 --> 00:32:50.187
[resident] Deveraux?

552
00:32:51.355 --> 00:32:54.191
Anna Deveraux.

553
00:32:54.274 --> 00:32:56.735
Hester. you look well.

554
00:32:57.569 --> 00:33:01.740
You still pining for the devil?

555
00:33:01.824 --> 00:33:04.076
I'm not Anna. ma'am.

556
00:33:04.159 --> 00:33:06.161
I know what you've done. honey.

557
00:33:06.245 --> 00:33:10.874
You sent him away.
'cause you was ashamed you wanted him.

558
00:33:10.958 --> 00:33:12.668
Come on. Mama. Let's go back to bed.

559
00:33:12.751 --> 00:33:13.794
- Hester. Hester.
- Huh?

560
00:33:13.877 --> 00:33:15.212
- How-How's Crystal doing?
- Oh. yeah.

561
00:33:16.338 --> 00:33:17.756
- [Hester] I'll tell you this.
- Yeah?

562
00:33:17.840 --> 00:33:21.885
Crystal. she is a damn sight better off
than she was in that clinic.

563
00:33:21.969 --> 00:33:24.096
- [Robert] Hester.
- She has got herself set up

564
00:33:24.179 --> 00:33:26.473
- real fine over by the river.
- [Robert] Hester.

565
00:33:26.557 --> 00:33:27.933
- The river?
- [winces]

566
00:33:28.016 --> 00:33:29.017
[Hester groans]

567
00:33:29.101 --> 00:33:30.269
Goddamn it!

568
00:33:31.687 --> 00:33:33.772
- [Robert] Yeah.
- I see you still love each other.

569
00:33:33.856 --> 00:33:35.441
Let's get the fuck out of here.

570
00:33:48.454 --> 00:33:49.496
Hey. Crystal.

571
00:33:50.414 --> 00:33:52.040
I got a little heads up for you.

572
00:33:54.710 --> 00:33:56.211
[Max] Sorry you had to see that.

573
00:33:57.671 --> 00:33:59.923
Sorry that you had to grow up with that.

574
00:34:00.674 --> 00:34:01.925
[Max] You must be hungry.

575
00:34:13.394 --> 00:34:14.813
[Natalie] What was she saying back there?

576
00:34:14.897 --> 00:34:17.274
Were you in love with my mom or something?

577
00:34:17.356 --> 00:34:18.941
[chuckles]

578
00:34:19.026 --> 00:34:20.486
"Or something." [chuckles]

579
00:34:23.030 --> 00:34:24.656
It's gonna be a long drive back.

580
00:34:26.200 --> 00:34:27.367
Are you not hungry?

581
00:34:27.993 --> 00:34:29.745
[sighs] I lost my appetite.

582
00:34:31.287 --> 00:34:33.289
[tense music playing]

583
00:34:42.423 --> 00:34:43.550
Is it good?

584
00:34:44.676 --> 00:34:45.843
Georgia peach.

585
00:34:46.762 --> 00:34:47.930
Yeah. We should go.

586
00:35:01.485 --> 00:35:02.945
It's a nice pool.

587
00:35:07.324 --> 00:35:09.827
That where you let the yard workers
and such come in?

588
00:35:09.910 --> 00:35:10.911
[Anna] Hmm.

589
00:35:12.913 --> 00:35:15.082
It's just a back gate.

590
00:35:18.418 --> 00:35:20.546
Damn. it's good to see you. Annie.

591
00:35:21.380 --> 00:35:22.840
You look taller than I remember.

592
00:35:23.632 --> 00:35:25.300
Well. I'm on the stairs. Dad.

593
00:35:26.093 --> 00:35:27.594
- [chuckles]
- Hmm.

594
00:35:27.678 --> 00:35:29.138
- And I shrunk.
- Hmm.

595
00:35:29.221 --> 00:35:30.848
You shrink when you get old.

596
00:35:31.473 --> 00:35:32.766
Gravity or something.

597
00:35:33.434 --> 00:35:34.852
You do look smaller than ever.

598
00:35:36.687 --> 00:35:40.065
I like to think the-the edges
are just worn off a little bit.

599
00:35:40.899 --> 00:35:41.900
[Anna] Mmm.

600
00:35:41.984 --> 00:35:42.985
Kids here?

601
00:35:43.944 --> 00:35:44.945
No.

602
00:35:55.038 --> 00:35:56.874
Look. I don't know what this is about.

603
00:35:56.957 --> 00:35:59.710
I'm just really glad that
you finally reached out.

604
00:36:04.590 --> 00:36:06.425
I have worked for this.

605
00:36:07.634 --> 00:36:10.220
And if there's anything that I can do

606
00:36:10.304 --> 00:36:13.807
to help get-get-get back your trust.
Annie. I'm…

607
00:36:15.517 --> 00:36:16.935
I'm here to do it.

608
00:36:20.522 --> 00:36:21.523
Okay.

609
00:36:22.024 --> 00:36:23.025
Let's talk.

610
00:36:26.612 --> 00:36:28.614
[suspenseful music playing]

611
00:36:39.124 --> 00:36:41.126
[music continues]

612
00:36:54.348 --> 00:36:55.432
Hello?

613
00:37:01.939 --> 00:37:03.065
Hello?

614
00:37:03.982 --> 00:37:05.984
[music continues]

615
00:38:09.131 --> 00:38:11.133
[music continues]

616
00:38:15.179 --> 00:38:16.597
[wood creaking]

617
00:38:27.858 --> 00:38:29.902
[Brandon] You know. six years ago.

618
00:38:30.944 --> 00:38:35.365
I cleaned up my act
and I moved to Savannah

619
00:38:36.366 --> 00:38:39.536
and I figured that sooner or later
you guys would give me a chance.

620
00:38:39.620 --> 00:38:42.956
Maybe the kids would come over.
watch a movie or something.

621
00:38:43.540 --> 00:38:47.961
And here you want me to break into
this guy's house and plant dope for you.

622
00:38:49.630 --> 00:38:53.091
Do you think if I had any better options.
I would have reached out to you? Hmm?

623
00:38:55.385 --> 00:38:57.596
- Maybe I shouldn't have.
- No. hey. hey. hey.

624
00:38:58.472 --> 00:38:59.932
I didn't say no.

625
00:39:01.475 --> 00:39:04.978
Look. Annie. I know that I wasn't
the best dad to you.

626
00:39:06.396 --> 00:39:08.482
You see. I'm not that guy anymore.

627
00:39:09.108 --> 00:39:12.111
Baby girl. if I do this and it blows up.

628
00:39:12.194 --> 00:39:14.696
I go back to prison
for the rest of my life.

629
00:39:16.406 --> 00:39:20.160
Sure. I can get a hold of some smack.
but right now I got a job.

630
00:39:20.702 --> 00:39:23.413
I got… I got a nice little place
in Garden City…

631
00:39:23.497 --> 00:39:25.415
Well. it's not as nice as this. but it's…

632
00:39:27.209 --> 00:39:28.669
I-I've got something to lose.

633
00:39:28.752 --> 00:39:30.295
This would be very simple.

634
00:39:31.171 --> 00:39:33.841
You place the drugs.
we call CrimeStoppers.

635
00:39:35.050 --> 00:39:36.593
McGruff the Crime Dog?

636
00:39:36.677 --> 00:39:37.928
[Tom] It's an anonymous line.

637
00:39:38.011 --> 00:39:40.389
The cops will show up. no questions asked.

638
00:39:40.472 --> 00:39:46.395
We have clients who got 20 years
just off a tip that was called in.

639
00:39:47.438 --> 00:39:48.856
[chuckles]

640
00:39:48.939 --> 00:39:51.233
And I thought you found it
in your heart to forgive me.

641
00:39:51.316 --> 00:39:53.235
[laughs]

642
00:39:55.737 --> 00:39:58.740
Hey. I guess we're not
so different after all. huh?

643
00:40:00.701 --> 00:40:02.411
- No. this was a mistake.
- [Brandon] Dinner.

644
00:40:05.038 --> 00:40:06.039
Once a month.

645
00:40:08.208 --> 00:40:10.252
You and me. Just so I can talk to you.

646
00:40:15.257 --> 00:40:17.593
And I get to see my grandkids.

647
00:40:18.886 --> 00:40:21.305
Do you really think
I would ever let you see my kids?

648
00:40:21.388 --> 00:40:23.724
You want something from me.
I want something from you.

649
00:40:33.609 --> 00:40:35.027
We're doing the right thing.

650
00:40:38.989 --> 00:40:40.574
[phone buzzing]

651
00:40:44.703 --> 00:40:45.996
Ray. how's it going up there?

652
00:40:46.079 --> 00:40:50.918
Listen. Val Tierney is not
the woman who was following you.

653
00:40:52.961 --> 00:40:56.548
The woman with the green jacket.
that was Crystal Cady.

654
00:40:56.632 --> 00:40:58.884
- [static on phone]
- Max Cady's half-sister.

655
00:40:59.635 --> 00:41:00.844
It's his sister?

656
00:41:01.553 --> 00:41:02.846
- Ray?
- Hello?

657
00:41:04.014 --> 00:41:05.390
- Hello?
- [line beeping]

658
00:41:07.559 --> 00:41:09.895
Max Cady's family
didn't come to the trial.

659
00:41:10.938 --> 00:41:12.940
His sister was institutionalized
back then.

660
00:41:13.023 --> 00:41:15.025
Why is she following him around now?

661
00:41:15.109 --> 00:41:16.110
I don't know.

662
00:41:17.569 --> 00:41:19.780
But it doesn't change what we need to do.

663
00:41:21.990 --> 00:41:23.992
[suspenseful music playing]

664
00:41:57.693 --> 00:41:59.027
[hammer cocks]

665
00:41:59.111 --> 00:42:01.113
[suspenseful music continues]

666
00:42:08.912 --> 00:42:09.913
[Max] Hey!

667
00:42:11.081 --> 00:42:13.083
What are you doing all the way up here?

668
00:42:14.084 --> 00:42:15.669
[Ray] Looking for the owner of a car.

669
00:42:17.504 --> 00:42:18.630
What about you?

670
00:42:20.424 --> 00:42:21.842
I grew up around here.

671
00:42:22.760 --> 00:42:24.094
- [Ray] Ah.
- [chuckles]

672
00:42:25.095 --> 00:42:26.597
[Ray] What are the chances?

673
00:42:28.265 --> 00:42:29.933
Did you find the owner?

674
00:42:32.060 --> 00:42:33.061
No.

675
00:42:33.979 --> 00:42:35.147
No one's in there.

676
00:42:36.482 --> 00:42:37.483
Oh.

677
00:42:38.525 --> 00:42:39.526
Well…

678
00:42:40.068 --> 00:42:41.236
That hurt?

679
00:42:42.905 --> 00:42:45.741
What? Uh. no. This thing don't hurt. no.

680
00:42:47.075 --> 00:42:48.076
Wow.

681
00:42:48.869 --> 00:42:50.078
Nice seeing you here.

682
00:42:51.205 --> 00:42:54.583
So the door was just open. right?

683
00:42:54.666 --> 00:42:56.418
And you can just go in?

684
00:42:57.002 --> 00:42:58.170
Take a look?

685
00:42:59.129 --> 00:43:00.172
But…

686
00:43:01.715 --> 00:43:02.841
you be careful.

687
00:43:03.717 --> 00:43:05.511
If you're not from around here…

688
00:43:06.512 --> 00:43:07.513
[clicks tongue]

689
00:43:08.639 --> 00:43:10.182
…it's easy to step on toes.

690
00:43:10.265 --> 00:43:11.642
[chuckles]

691
00:43:14.103 --> 00:43:17.731
Hey. Max. you know what
the greatest feeling in the world is?

692
00:43:18.857 --> 00:43:19.942
Letting go.

693
00:43:21.110 --> 00:43:22.444
Whatever shit you've been through.

694
00:43:23.028 --> 00:43:24.696
whatever pain. whatever loss.

695
00:43:25.322 --> 00:43:27.741
just let it go.

696
00:43:33.372 --> 00:43:34.456
Uh-huh.

697
00:43:34.957 --> 00:43:37.584
Anyway. I should get going.

698
00:43:38.418 --> 00:43:39.503
Long drive.

699
00:43:40.212 --> 00:43:42.548
Why the hurry? Let me buy you a drink.

700
00:43:42.631 --> 00:43:43.924
I know a place up the road.

701
00:43:44.508 --> 00:43:45.759
How about a rain check?

702
00:43:48.637 --> 00:43:49.930
That Natalie?

703
00:43:51.348 --> 00:43:53.225
- Natalie!
- R-Ray. Ray.

704
00:43:53.308 --> 00:43:55.060
- [gunshots]
- [groans]

705
00:43:56.103 --> 00:43:57.521
Okay. [shushes]

706
00:43:59.106 --> 00:44:01.358
[shushes]

707
00:44:01.442 --> 00:44:02.484
You were right. You were right.

708
00:44:02.568 --> 00:44:05.154
"Just let go."

709
00:44:06.530 --> 00:44:10.367
[Ray groaning]

710
00:44:39.313 --> 00:44:40.939
Where are we?

711
00:44:41.023 --> 00:44:42.024
[Max] Hey.

712
00:44:44.651 --> 00:44:46.278
What happened?

713
00:44:46.361 --> 00:44:47.446
You fell asleep.

714
00:44:56.747 --> 00:44:57.790
What is that?

715
00:44:58.499 --> 00:45:00.542
- Careful. Careful. Careful.
- Whoa.

716
00:45:03.712 --> 00:45:06.548
The world's a bit better place
with you in it. okay?

717
00:45:06.632 --> 00:45:07.966
[Natalie breathes shakily]

718
00:45:10.344 --> 00:45:11.345
What?

719
00:45:17.267 --> 00:45:18.268
What?

720
00:45:22.439 --> 00:45:24.691
When did they find your wife's body?

721
00:45:28.320 --> 00:45:29.363
Why?

722
00:45:30.155 --> 00:45:32.241
You said something changed after…

723
00:45:35.077 --> 00:45:36.662
they found her body. and my mom…

724
00:45:38.747 --> 00:45:42.292
took you in. what. that summer of 2008?

725
00:45:46.755 --> 00:45:48.590
And you said that you were close.

726
00:45:51.969 --> 00:45:53.804
And that you had feelings for her.

727
00:45:58.642 --> 00:45:59.768
October.

728
00:46:00.811 --> 00:46:01.979
2008.

729
00:46:08.152 --> 00:46:09.736
I was born July.

730
00:46:11.822 --> 00:46:13.073
2009.

731
00:46:18.412 --> 00:46:19.746
Tom's not my dad.

732
00:46:21.373 --> 00:46:22.583
Neither is Paul.

733
00:46:23.417 --> 00:46:24.418
No.

734
00:46:25.169 --> 00:46:26.170
[sighs]

735
00:46:29.256 --> 00:46:30.591
[exhales]

736
00:46:30.674 --> 00:46:34.636
Listen. I didn't want to see you
when I was in a cage.

737
00:46:34.720 --> 00:46:35.721
[Natalie sighs]

738
00:46:37.139 --> 00:46:40.851
But I've never stopped thinking about you.

739
00:46:41.810 --> 00:46:42.853
Natalie.

740
00:47:02.915 --> 00:47:05.584
[breathing heavily]

741
00:47:30.651 --> 00:47:32.236
[breathes shakily]

742
00:47:41.328 --> 00:47:42.329
[inhales sharply]

743
00:48:06.770 --> 00:48:08.355
I don't feel different.

744
00:48:09.690 --> 00:48:11.358
That's because you haven't changed.

745
00:48:15.320 --> 00:48:16.947
You are who you've always been.

746
00:48:21.785 --> 00:48:23.203
[Natalie sighs]

747
00:48:26.123 --> 00:48:27.666
- Come on. Let's go home.
- [sobbing]

748
00:48:27.749 --> 00:48:29.751
[thunder rumbles]

749
00:48:32.838 --> 00:48:34.256
[Natalie sniffles]

750
00:48:34.339 --> 00:48:36.341
[crickets chirping]

751
00:48:45.350 --> 00:48:48.312
I can't believe she didn't take
a paternity test.

752
00:48:48.395 --> 00:48:49.813
[sighs]

753
00:48:54.610 --> 00:48:56.028
[car door opens]

754
00:49:10.292 --> 00:49:11.710
Maybe this will help you.

755
00:49:17.216 --> 00:49:18.383
[sighs]

756
00:49:21.303 --> 00:49:22.429
Thank you.

757
00:49:24.890 --> 00:49:26.183
Oh. wait. Wait.

758
00:49:26.266 --> 00:49:28.268
Your bag. Don't forget your bag.

759
00:49:29.770 --> 00:49:30.854
Oh. I can…

760
00:49:35.484 --> 00:49:36.985
- What?
- [Max sighs]

761
00:49:55.087 --> 00:49:56.088
[car door closes]

762
00:50:15.524 --> 00:50:18.527
[door opens. closes]

763
00:50:20.195 --> 00:50:22.781
Natalie. what are you doing home?

764
00:50:24.825 --> 00:50:27.077
I hate sleeping at Paul's.
so I took an Uber.

765
00:50:35.127 --> 00:50:36.545
Are we doing this?

766
00:50:37.337 --> 00:50:39.339
We're just playing his game against him.

767
00:50:39.965 --> 00:50:41.383
Let's see how he likes it.

768
00:50:46.889 --> 00:50:50.142
[beeping]

769
00:50:51.018 --> 00:50:52.603
[line ringing]

770
00:50:52.686 --> 00:50:54.438
[operator]
CrimeStoppers anonymous tip line.

771
00:50:54.521 --> 00:50:56.648
I want to report
a large quantity of narcotics

772
00:50:56.732 --> 00:50:58.567
in a house on West Jones Street.
